Fennec.</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Erik Vold</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 13 Dec 2012 07:34:37 -0800</pubDate><guid>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/copy-link/versions/2.1</guid></item><item><title>Image Exposer 0.1</title><link>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/image-exposer/</link><description>Sometimes you want to share an image with a friend or just save it to your device.  That's when Firefox's context menu (right-click) is extremely helpful - but on FF Mobile there's no equivalent.  This add-on gives users a way to view all the images on a page, then either view them directly, copy the URL to the clipboard, send a link to the image via e-mail, or save the image.</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">mausmalone</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 11 Feb 2011 10:14:00 -0800</pubDate><guid>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/image-exposer/versions/0.1</guid></item><item><title>Reopen last closed tab 0.2.2</title><link>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/reopen-last-closed-tab/</link><description>I hope it's easy enough to use; I have only desktop Fennec, so I don't know whether it's comfortable enough on a mobile.

With this add-on a tab is not closed, but hidden; when you "close" another tab, hidden tab is closed and "closed" tab is hidden.

When you see one tab with close button on it, it means presence of a second, hidden, tab. To close it, close the one tab you see and reopen it. It will be without close-button: there is no hidden tab.</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Wikiwide</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 10 Sep 2010 09:59:51 -0700</pubDate><guid>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/reopen-last-closed-tab/versions/0.2.2</guid></item><item><title>Find in Page 0.15</title><link>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/find-in-page/</link><description>After typing the search keyword in the URL bar, clicking the page search button results in the keyword being searched for and highlighted on the current webpage. To search for multiple keywords, separate them with '|'.

Interface is different in the two last versions:
&amp;lt;pre&amp;gt;
0.10 (Fennec prior to 2.0) : The button for page search is located at the left of the search engines panel.
0.12 (Fennec 2.0+)         : The button for page search is located at the bottom of search engines list.
0.13 (Fennec 4.0+)         : The search may be conducted in all open tabs simultaneously.
&amp;lt;/pre&amp;gt;

The options of the add-on are:
1. Highlight colour? (green/red);
2. Clear of the previous search's highlight before next search? (yes/no);
3. Use the selected text as the keyword? (yes/no);
4. Match case? (yes/no);
5. Only current tab? (yes/no).</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Wikiwide</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 09 Sep 2011 14:55:24 -0700</pubDate><guid>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/find-in-page/versions/0.15</guid></item><item><title>Hold4Tab 0.21</title><link>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/hold4tab/</link><description>In order to open a hyper-link in a new tab, press on the link for a second and a half and the link will be opened in a new tab.</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Almog B</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 19 Jan 2010 13:09:30 -0800</pubDate><guid>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/hold4tab/versions/0.21</guid></item><item><title>Tabs Utility 1.8</title><link>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/tabs-utility/</link><description>&lt;strong&gt;
&lt;a href="http://outgoing.mozilla.org/v1/d1d4cdae857cc20ab829d17158e31ac050dcaeac/http%3A//missmobile.wordpress.com/2010/05/10/mobile-add-ons-challenge-winners-announced/" title="** Winner of Mozilla Mobile Add-ons Challenge! **"&gt;** Winner of Mozilla Mobile Add-ons Challenge! **&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/strong&gt;
You can see &lt;a href="http://outgoing.mozilla.org/v1/1dbd17d0b0a671da5d5d4b0434453e1255cbab84/http%3A//www.youtube.com/watch%3Fv%3D7vTda2uC3xA" title="Tabs Utility for Firefox for Mobile on Nokia N900"&gt;this demonstrating video.&lt;/a&gt; 

This extension contains some utilities to organize your tabs:
- drag and drop of tabs: you can now put them where you want (VERY USEFUL)
- session restore (VERY USEFUL)
- sort of tabs by domain
- sort of tabs by last visit (USEFUL)

Options:
- hide www button: hide/show the sort by domain button
- hide clock button: hide/show the sort by last visit button
- Session restore: you can choose
   a) Automatically restore (it restore session without questions)
   b) Ask before restore (when you launch Fennec it asks you if you want to restore tabs)
   c) Don't restore session (it saves the last session but don't restore)
   d) Don't even save session (disable session restore) </description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Enrico Previdi</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 11 May 2010 14:50:22 -0700</pubDate><guid>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/tabs-utility/versions/1.8</guid></item><item><title>InstaFox 0.3</title><link>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/instafox/</link><description>InstaFox is a simple extensions for Firefox for Mobile that enables using the Instapaper service.

Instapaper is a service that allows one to save webspages or articles for later reading. It's especially useful on a mobile device since one can read the websites in simple text form or even as ePub-files.

Using InstaFox it's easy to save webpages to Instapaper by pressing the "Save to Instapaper" -button in the page actions menu. You can access Instapaper by pressing the Instapaper-icon on the left sidebar.</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Juhana Jauhiainen</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 16 Feb 2011 14:47:44 -0800</pubDate><guid>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/instafox/versions/0.3</guid></item><item><title>Copy URL 1.2.4</title><link>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/copy-url-252534/</link><description>Copy URL is the "little brother" of the &lt;a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/197224/" rel="nofollow"&gt;Copy ShortURL&lt;/a&gt; add-on.

This add-on adds a menu item "Copy URL" to the right-click menu, which copies the current page's URL to the clipboard. It also adds a button to the "add-ons bar" at the bottom of the browser, with the same functionality.</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Fred Wenzel</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 17 Jun 2013 12:41:34 -0700</pubDate><guid>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/copy-url-252534/versions/1.2.4</guid></item><item><title>readability 0.6</title><link>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/readability-47136/</link><description>This add-on is an adaptation of the readability bookmarklet available  at &lt;a href="http://outgoing.mozilla.org/v1/7d25068ba45d3faf5088936a6dae418300e5f56a/http%3A//lab.arc90.com/experiments/readability/."&gt;http://lab.arc90.com/experiments/readability/.&lt;/a&gt;

It allows you to clean up article pages for your reading pleasure.</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Fabrice Desré</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 30 Aug 2010 05:49:27 -0700</pubDate><guid>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/readability-47136/versions/0.6</guid></item><item><title>Home Links 2.3</title><link>https://addons.mozilla.org/EN-US/mobile/addon/home-links/</link><description>With this add-on you can quickly open your favorite links.
If you saved more than one link, when you click the home button it asks you which link you want to open.
The link you chose is open in a new tab.

&lt;b&gt;Winner of Mobile Add-ons Cup!&lt;/b&gt;

Thanks to votes, &lt;a href="http://outgoing.mozilla.org/v1/bc736f223d2b012fc9dfdad5bd0fd03415e1ce5859a9d1e62e436b78adca001b/http%3A//blog.mozilla.com/mobile/2011/02/18/home-links-add-on-wins-peoples-choice-vote/" rel="nofollow" title="Home Links Add-on Wins People’s Choice Vote!"&gt;Home Links Add-on Wins People’s Choice Vote! &lt;/a&gt;

If you want to delete a link of the add on, you can follow these steps:
1 - open the menu
2 - click on "Tools"
3 - click on "Add-ons"
4 - click on the "Home Links" add on
5 - select the link you want to delete from the field "Link settings" and then click on the button "Delete" on the right

